      { heading: "Eminönü Pier — Main Departure Point for Shared Cruises", content: "Eminönü is Istanbul's primary cruise departure point, located at the southern end of the Galata Bridge in the historic Fatih district. This is where most shared Bosphorus cruises — including the popular [Bosphorus sightseeing cruise](/cruises/bosphorus-sightseeing-cruise) — depart from. The pier is easily accessible by the T1 tram — just get off at the Eminönü stop and walk 2 minutes toward the waterfront. The area is unmistakable: you will see dozens of tour boats, the famous fish sandwich boats (balık ekmek), and the Egyptian Spice Bazaar directly behind the pier. When you book with MerrySails, your confirmation email includes the exact pier number and a Google Maps pin. For dinner cruises, the transfer vehicle drops you directly at the boarding point, so you do not need to navigate the area yourself. Eminönü can be busy and chaotic — arrive 15 minutes early and ignore street touts trying to redirect you to different boats. Walk directly to your confirmed pier number." },
      { heading: "Kuruçeşme — Bosphorus Cruise Departure for Yachts", content: "[Private yacht charters](/cruises/yacht-charter-in-istanbul) with MerrySails depart from Kuruçeşme Marina, an upscale marina on the European shore between Ortaköy and Bebek. This location is away from the tourist crowds of Eminönü and offers a more exclusive experience from the moment you arrive. The marina has parking, clean facilities, and a calm atmosphere suited to private events. Getting to Kuruçeşme: take a taxi (about 15–20 minutes from Taksim, 25–30 minutes from Sultanahmet) or the bus from Kabataş along the coastal road. The marina address and Google Maps pin are included in your booking confirmation. For yacht charters, arriving 10 minutes before your scheduled time allows the crew to welcome you aboard and brief you on the vessel." , expertQuote: { text: "İstanbul'daki kalkış noktaları arasında en merkezi ve erişilebilir olanı Eminönü'dür. Tramvay hattına doğrudan bağlantısı sayesinde her otelden kolayca ulaşılabilir.", author: "Nihan Erdoğan", title: "İstanbul Turist Rehberi, Kültür Bakanlığı Lisanslı" }},
      { heading: "Kabataş and Other Departure Points", content: "Kabataş pier, located at the end of the T1 tram line and the start of the funicular to Taksim Square, is another common departure point for certain Bosphorus cruises. It is particularly convenient for guests staying in Taksim or Beyoğlu. The area is modern and well-organized compared to the historic chaos of Eminönü. Some cruises also depart from Ortaköy (near the iconic mosque), from Beşiktaş pier, or from Karaköy near the Galata Bridge. Each departure point has its own character — Ortaköy is trendy and artistic, Beşiktaş is bustling and local, and Karaköy combines hip cafes with maritime history. Your booking confirmation will always specify the exact departure point, so there is no guesswork involved." },
      { heading: "How to Reach Bosphorus Cruise Departure Points", content: "From Sultanahmet (Blue Mosque area): Eminönü is a 10-minute walk downhill or one T1 tram stop. From Taksim/Beyoğlu: Take the funicular to Kabataş (2 minutes), then the T1 tram to Eminönü (15 minutes). Alternatively, Kabataş pier departures save you the extra tram ride. From Karaköy/Galata: A 5-minute walk to Eminönü or Karaköy pier. From Beşiktaş: Walk to the Beşiktaş pier or take a short taxi to Kuruçeşme Marina. From the Asian side (Kadıköy/Üsküdar): Take the ferry to Eminönü (15–20 minutes) — the ferry ride itself is a mini Bosphorus preview. Istanbul's public transport is affordable and efficient — an Istanbulkart (rechargeable transit card) works on trams, buses, ferries, and the metro." , expertQuote: { text: "Boğaz'da 30 yıldır seyr-i sefer yapıyorum. Her gün geçişte farklı bir ışık, farklı bir atmosfer var. Bu deneyimi bir kez yaşayan, İstanbul'u gerçek anlamda tanımış olur.", author: "Kaptan Mehmet Akın", title: "Denizcilik Uzmanı, 30 Yıllık Kaptan" }},
      { heading: "Arrival Tips at Bosphorus Cruise Departure Piers", content: "Regardless of your departure point, a few tips ensure a smooth boarding experience. Arrive 15 minutes early — this gives time to check in, use facilities, and find your seat. Have your booking confirmation ready (digital or printed). For [Bosphorus dinner cruises](/cruises/bosphorus-dinner-cruise) with hotel pickup, be in the hotel lobby at the specified time — the vehicle will not wait long. At Eminönü, be aware of touts approaching with 'special offers' — they are not affiliated with your booked operator. Walk directly to your confirmed pier number. The boarding process is straightforward: show your confirmation, receive a boarding pass, and walk aboard. Crew members will direct you to your seat or table. Most vessels have both indoor and outdoor seating — early arrivals get first choice." }
